I"¤	<p>This feature requires <strong>two steps</strong> one on <strong>Facebook side</strong> and one on <strong>Yclas side</strong>:</p>

<h2 id="facebook-side">Facebook side</h2>

<p><strong>(might change depending on Facebook!)</strong></p>

<ol>
  <li>First you need to <strong>log in to Facebook</strong> and go to https://developers.facebook.com</li>
  <li>Click on <strong>Apps</strong> (register as a developer if you havenâ€™t already)</li>
</ol>

<p><a href="//open-classifieds.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/facebook-apps-1024x516.png" class="thumbnail gallery-item" data-gallery="">
<img src="//open-classifieds.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/facebook-apps-1024x516.png" alt="facebook apps" /> 
</a></p>

<p>3. Click on <strong>New App</strong> and name it whatever you want</p>

<p><a href="//open-classifieds.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/facebook-apps2-1024x516.png" class="thumbnail gallery-item" data-gallery="">
<img src="//open-classifieds.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/facebook-apps2-1024x516.png" alt="facebook apps2" /> 
</a></p>

<p>4. <strong>Copy the App ID</strong> that shows up after creation</p>

<p><a href="//open-classifieds.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/Facebook-apps3-1024x516.png" class="thumbnail gallery-item" data-gallery="">
<img src="//open-classifieds.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/05/Facebook-apps3-1024x516.png" alt="Facebook apps3" />
</a></p>

<h2 id="yclas-side">Yclas side</h2>

<ol>
  <li>Log in to your <strong>admin panel</strong>.</li>
  <li>Go to <strong>Settings</strong> &gt; <strong>Advertisement</strong> &gt; <strong>Advertisement Display Options</strong>.</li>
  <li>Enter the <strong>Facebook App ID</strong> into the <strong>Facebook comments</strong> box.</li>
  <li>Press <strong>Save</strong>!</li>
</ol>

<p><a href="//docs.yclas.com/images/facebook-comments.png" class="thumbnail gallery-item" data-gallery="">
<img src="//docs.yclas.com/images/facebook-comments.png" alt="How to add Facebook comments" /> 
</a></p>

<p>Now you have fully functional facebook comments on your ads.</p>

